).svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Hungary (1920\u20131946)|Hungary]]\n|[[Mikl\u00f3s Horthy]] as [[Regent of Hungary|Regent]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|1946\n|Decision of the parliament without a referendum.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Italy (1861-1946).svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Italy|Italy]]\n|[[Umberto II of Italy|Umberto II]]\n|Referendum; official result: 54.3% in favour of republic.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Bulgaria.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Bulgaria|Bulgaria]]\n|[[Simeon Saxe-Coburg-Gotha|Simeon II]]\n|Referendum held to decide whether the monarchy would be retained; 95% in favour of republic. Simeon later served as [[Prime Minister of Bulgaria]] 2001-2005.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of the Kingdom of Sarawak (1870).svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Sarawak|Sarawak]]\n|[[Charles Vyner Brooke]]\n|[[White Rajahs]] hand over power to British crown.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Romania.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Romania|Romania]]\n|[[Michael I of Romania|Michael I]]\n|1947\n|Forced out by the communists.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Ireland.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n|George VI\n|1949\n|Abolished the last \"[[Monarchy of Ireland]]\", the King of the United Kingdom.\n|-\n!colspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#eeeeaa;\"|1950s\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of India.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Dominion of India|India]]\n|George VI\n|1950\n|Abolished [[Commonwealth realm|Commonwealth monarchy]].\n|-\n|[[File:Jaisalmer_Flag.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Jaisalmer State|Jaisalmer]]\n|Giridhar Singh Bhati\n|1950\n|The [[Jaisalmer State|Kingdom of Jaisalmer]] merged with the [[Republic of India]] in 1950.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Mysore.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Mysore|Mysore]]\n|[[Jayachamaraja Wodeyar]]\n|1950\n|The [[Kingdom of Mysore]] merged with the [[Republic of India]] in 1950\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Tibet.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Tibet (1912-51)|Tibet]]\n|[[14th Dalai Lama|Tenzin Gyatso]]\n|1951\n|[[Incorporation of Tibet into the People's Republic of China|Incorporated]] into the [[China|People's Republic of China]].\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Egypt 1922.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Egypt|Egypt]] \n|[[Fuad II of Egypt|Fuad II]]\n|1953\n|Republic proclaimed one year after the [[Egyptian Revolution of 1952|1952 Coup d'\u00e9tat]].\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Vietnam.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[North Vietnam|Vietnam]]\n|[[B\u1ea3o \u0110\u1ea1i]]\n|1954\n|Vietnam partitioned through the [[Geneva Conference (1954)|Geneva Accords]].\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of South Vietnam.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[State of Vietnam|Vietnam]]\n|[[B\u1ea3o \u0110\u1ea1i]]\n|1955\n|Referendum in South Vietnam.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Pakistan.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Dominion of Pakistan|Pakistan]]\n|[[Elizabeth II]]\n|1956\n|Abolished [[Commonwealth realm|Commonwealth monarchy]].\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Tunisia.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Beylik of Tunis|Tunisia]]\n|[[Muhammad VIII al-Amin]]\n|1957\n|Decision of the parliament.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Iraq (1921\u20131959).svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Iraq|Iraq]]\n|[[Faisal II of Iraq|Faisal II]]\n|1958\n|[[14 July Revolution|coup d'\u00e9tat]]\n|-\n!colspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#eeeeaa;\"|1960s\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Ghana.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[History of Ghana#Independence|Ghana]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Elizabeth II\n|1960\n|Abolished [[Commonwealth realm|Commonwealth monarchy]], following a [[1960 Ghanaian constitutional referendum|referendum]]; official result: 88% in favour of republic.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of South Africa 1928-1994.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Union of South Africa|South Africa]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1961\n|Abolished [[Commonwealth realm|Commonwealth monarchy]] pursuant to [[1960 South African republic referendum|1960 referendum]]; official result: 53% in favor of republic.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag Rwanda 1959.svg|31px|border]]\n|[[Kingdom of Rwanda|Rwanda]]\n|[[Kigeli V]]\n|coup d'\u00e9tat, followed by [[1961 Rwandan monarchy referendum|referendum]]; official result: 80% in favor of abolishing monarchy.\n|-\n|[[File:Flag of Tanganyika (1961\u20131964).svg|31px|border]]\